Document: AABB  
Path: godot/classes/class_aabb.rst  
Summary: Properties of the AABB class (end, position, size) and their relationships, including usage notes and method references.  

- end (Vector3): The ending point. This is usually the corner on the top-right and back of the bounding box, and is equivalent to position + size. Setting this point affects the size property. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).  

- position (Vector3): The origin point. This is usually the corner on the bottom-left and forward of the bounding box. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).  

- size (Vector3): The bounding box's width, height, and depth starting from position. Setting this value also affects the end point. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0). Note: It's recommended setting the width, height, and depth to non-negative values. This is because most methods in Godot assume that the position is the bottom-left-forward corner, and the end is the top-right-back corner. To get an equivalent bounding box with non-negative size, use the abs() method.
---CHUNK---
Document: AABB
Path: godot/classes/class_aabb.rst
Summary: Constructor methods for creating AABB objects with different parameters

Method: AABB() → creates an AABB with position and size set to Vector3.ZERO. The constructed box has no dimensions and is positioned at the origin.

Method: AABB(from: AABB) → creates a copy of the provided AABB instance. The new box shares the same position and size values as the source.

Method: AABB(position: Vector3, size: Vector3) → creates an AABB using the specified position and size parameters. Position defines the box's origin, size determines its dimensions along each axis.
