Document: AABB  
Path: godot/classes/class_aabb.rst  
Summary: Operator methods for comparing AABB objects and transforming them with Transform3D matrices.  

Operator != (AABB): Returns true if the position or size of both bounding boxes are not equal. Note: Due to floating-point precision errors, consider using is_equal_approx() instead, which is more reliable.  

Operator * (Transform3D): Inversely transforms (multiplies) the AABB by the given Transform3D matrix, assuming the transformation basis is orthonormal (rotation/reflection allowed, scaling/skew not allowed). "aabb * transform" is equivalent to "transform.inverse() * aabb". For affine transformations (with scaling), use "transform.affine_inverse() * aabb" instead.  

Operator == (AABB): Returns true if both position and size of the bounding boxes are exactly equal. Note: Due to floating-point precision errors, consider using is_equal_approx() instead, which is more reliable.